cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.CV, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is likely because the paper discusses the importance of consumer tests and the customers' point of view in evaluating active safety features. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is likely because the paper focuses on the systematic generation of test scenarios and the investigation of the influence of different test parameters on the system's performance. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is likely because the paper presents a formal model using a graph to represent the allowed variances and uses simulation environments to process test cases. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is possible because the paper mentions the extension of Autonomous Emergency Braking/Forward Collision Warning systems to pedestrian detection scenarios. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is possible because the paper discusses the evaluation of active safety systems in different test cases representing different trajectories and velocities, which could be related to robotics applications.
